<lyrics>[V1]
 Why should I feel discouraged
 Why should the shadows come
 Why then should my heart be lonely
 And longing for heaven and home

[V2]
 With Jesus as my portion
 A constant friend is He
 For His eye is on the sparrow
 And I know he watches over me
 His eye is on the sparrow
 And I know he watches me

[V3]
 I sing because I'm happy
 I sing because I'm free
 His eye is on the sparrow
 And I know he watches
 He watches over me
 You know
 Sing because I'm happy
 I sing because I'm free
 His eye is on the sparrow
 And I know he watches
 He watches over me

[V4]
 I sing (yes He watches me)
 He watches me (yes He watches me)
 When I'm up (yes He watches me)
 When I'm down (yes He watches me)
 When I'm lonely (yes He watches me)
 Yes He's near (yes He watches me)
 Yes He's near (yes He watches me)
 Yes He's near (yes He watches me)

[V5]
 He has promised &quot;I'm with you&quot;
 What He said then He will do

[V6]
 Amazing love this is true
 He loves me and loves you too

[V7]
 I say yeah (yeah)
 Yeah (yeah)...

[V8]
 Yes He watches me
 Yes He watches me</lyrics>
<title>His eye is on the sparrow</title>
